commands.weather.set.clear: Can't you tell I got news for you? The sun is shining and so are you.
gamerule.defaultFormatting.description: The colour used mainly for feedback from commands.
gamerule.secondaryFormatting.description: The colour used for special parts of feedback from commands.
gamerule.doMelt.description: Whether ice and snow should melt.
gamerule.maxHomes.description: The amount of homes you can set, 0 disables homes completely, -1 is infinite.
gamerule.doSilkSpawners.description: Whether spawners should drop when mined with silk touch.
gamerule.randomOrderPlayerTick.descripti: Whether players should be ticked in a random order rather than starting at whomever joined first. Makes things like dropparties more fair.
gamerule.hopperTransferCooldown.descript: The amount of ticks a hopper waits between each item transfer.
gamerule.hopperTransferRate.description: The amount of items a hopper transfers at a time.
gamerule.doFarmlandTrample.description: Whether farmland should turn to dirt when jumped on.
gamerule.doJoinMessage.description: Whether a message should be sent when a player joins or leaves the server.
gamerule.doExplosions.description: Whether explosions should destroy blocks and damage entities.
gamerule.wildLimit.description: The maximum amount of blocks the wild command should teleport players to.
gamerule.tpaTimeout.description: The amount of ticks it takes for a TPA request to timeout.
gamerule.fluidsInfinite.description: Whether all fluids can create new source blocks like water.
gamerule.doLiquidFlow.description: Whether liquids should flow or stay stationary.
gamerule.vaultRows.description: The amount of rows vaults may have.
gamerule.vaults.description: How many vaults each player has. Set to 0 to disable vaults.
gamerule.nicknameLimit.description: The maximum amount of characters excluding formattings a nickname may have.
gamerule.doSignColours.description: Whether normal players may use colours on signs. Operators ignore this value.
gamerule.doBookColours.description: Whether normal players may use colours in books. Operators ignore this value.
gamerule.doChatColours.description: Whether normal players may use colours in chat messages. Operators ignore this value.
gamerule.doItemColours.description: Whether normal players may use colours in item names. Operators ignore this value.
gamerule.doEnchantLevelLimit.description: Whether the maximum level you may enchant items with using an enchantment table should be capped at level 30.
gamerule.doPriorWorkPenalty.description: Whether altering an item in an anvil should make the next alteration more expensive.
gamerule.doItemsFireDamage.description: Whether item entities should sustain fire damage.
gamerule.doPathFinding.description: Whether mobs should walk around your world.
gamerule.doGoals.description: Whether mobs should have goals. (Aka AI)
gamerule.doStacktrace.description: Whether errors should be printed to the console when one gets thrown while running a command.
gamerule.sendCommandFeedbackToOps.descri: Whether feedback from commands should be sent to other operators.
gamerule.doChair.description: Whether stairs may act as chairs when right-clicked on.
commands.data.item.get: %s on item stack %s after scale factor of %s is %s
